          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>The results show elevated hemoglobin and hematocrit, which may suggest relative or absolute erythrocytosis; further clinical correlation and assessment of hydration status are recommended. Platelet distribution width is also increased, which may indicate platelet anisocytosis but with normal platelet count. Other parameters are within normal limits. No acute cytopenias or leukocytosis detected.</td></tr></table></div>"
